channel.description:
Was bored, So I made this. Yes 100% By me. [IMG]http://i666.photobucket.com/albums/vv23/uberxgod/fw.jpg[/img] Some pics of me animating it. [IMG]http://i666.photobucket.com/albums/vv23/uberxgod/anim1.jpg[/img]
The fire is going to be a bitch to animate. But as it is atm works 100%.
*Update* 100% overall working now :), 100% client campatable too <- Means I did not have to add it in multiple models E.G Dragons, Corp beast ect. [IMG]http://i666.photobucket.com/albums/vv23/uberxgod/pic.jpg[/img] Atm working on special attacks for it, Thinking of a Fire ranged. DAMN JAGEX FOR TAKING MY IDEAS! *Update* Added a ingame picture of the Special Attack I made for him. The special attack is 100% animated. [IMG]http://i666.photobucket.com/albums/vv23/uberxgod/specpic.jpg[/img] [IMG]http://i666.photobucket.com/albums/vv23/uberxgod/specpic2.jpg[/img] *Update* Video added of the GFX, Just a simple GFX test. So I threw in a junk anim. [URL=http://s666.photobucket.com/albums/vv23/uberxgod/?action=view&current=fin.mp4][IMG]http://i666.photobucket.com/albums/vv23/uberxgod/th_fin.jpg[/img][/URL] ^Click on the picture for the Video^

@badger41 wrote:

Datmaker is not a very good tool to use when animating. Sometimes it will leave blanks in the animation data and the model will glitch a little.

Animating manually is alot easier than most make it out to be, the model is only as hard to animate as how complicated the model itself is.

item.title: Tormented Warrior [S.O]
item.dc:creator: @man_killerx man_killerx
item.description:
@man_killerx wrote:

Body is never 0. That is one error on the Tutorial’s pics. Body is this (From my notes)
PRI: 4 < (If NPC It is 1)
TSKIN: 4
VSKIN1: 8

Then you would have different ones for the shoulders.

I have figured out the fire, I just gave each tip a differen Weigt value. Then moved each one randomly while moving the smaller peices randomly also to create a fire look.[quote=“CoonHunter, post:12, topic:351731”][quote author=the wanderer link=topic=448085.msg3288616#msg3288616 date=1280378668]
Shouldn’t the platebody be 0, or is that TSKINS? And when Jagex creates fires the create like 3 different orbs and then just change the alpha of them. If you need a picture I’ll show you it. Other than that pretty good.
[/quote]
Corrected

@TOPIC - Actually very good, but as you said above, yes, this will be a bitch to animate. I suggest using DatMaker for the gloves, hands, and headgear, but as for the skirt (i think?) and platebody, it will require manual animating.[/quote]

Animating basic body parts is very easy for me to do :P. Datmaker is 95% useless to me now. All I need it for is to render .MQO to .Dat.

Read full topic
